about.summary: Lazy Out-of-core dataframes and visualization for large (~billion rows/objects) tabular datasets

app.summary: Lazy Out-of-core dataframes and visualization for large (~billion rows/objects) tabular datasets

name: vaex
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "vaex" %}
{% set version = "2.6.0" %}
{% set sha256 = "7ce491f7fcfe37d407ee04f1de74d14edbd02175ea0b6270d1c370c1e0cebbb3" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python

requirements:
  build:
    - python >=3.6
    - setuptools
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - vaex-core >=1.5.0,<2
    - vaex-viz >=0.3.8,<0.4
    - vaex-server >=0.2.1,<0.3
    - vaex-hdf5 >=0.5.6,<0.6
    - vaex-astro >=0.6.1,<0.7
    - vaex-arrow >=0.4.2,<0.5
    - vaex-jupyter >=0.4.1,<0.5
    - vaex-ml >=0.8,<0.9
    # - vaex-distributed
    # - vaex-ui
    # - vaex-graphql

test:
  imports:
    - vaex
    - vaex.file

app:
  entry: vaex
  icon: logo.png
  summary: Lazy Out-of-core dataframes and visualization for large (~billion rows/objects) tabular datasets
  type: desk

about:
  home: https://vaex.io
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: 'Lazy Out-of-core dataframes and visualization for large (~billion rows/objects) tabular datasets'
  doc_url: https://docs.vaex.io

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - maartenbreddels
